result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Julie Christie Toth in court with attorney Peter Christopher Lloyd. Daniel R. Hess appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
8:49 a.m. ADA Hess calls the case and states the appearances.
Cases being heard today are  16CF410 and 16CM144.

Plea questionnaire/Agreement filed.
Prosecutor states plea agreement. and conditions of Deferred Prosecution Agreement.
Attorney for Defendant concurs with agreement stated.

Defendant enters a plea of: 

16CF410
Count 1: No Contest

Count 2: DRI

16CM144:
Count 1: DRI


Court questions Defendant regarding plea.
Court informs Defendant of Constitutional Rights. Court advises Defendant of Elements State must prove for the Charge.
Court questions Attorney for Defendant.
Court finds Defendant's Plea is freely, voluntarily and intelligently made.
Attorneys stipulate that there is factual basis for the charge(s).

BY THE COURT:
Court finds a sufficient factual basis to support the charge(s).
Court finds the defendant guilty of 16CF410 Count 1, but will withhold the entry of judgment pursuant to the Deferred Prosecution Agreement. 16CF410 Count 2 and 16CM144 are dismissed and read-in. 

ADA Hess makes sentencing statements to the Court. 
State has complied with Victim Notification Statutes.
Atty Lloyd concurs with the sentencing statements made by ADA Hess.

BY THE COURT:
Deferred Prosecution Agreement is approved for 12 months.
Court will wait for the dismissal of this matter.
Plea hearing on April 21, 2017 at 08:30 am.
Pre-trial conference on April 3, 2017 at 09:00 am.
